cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SI, cs.CL

The paper proposes a novel framework for learning convolutional neural networks on arbitrary graphs, which is a topic that falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed method involves attentional layers, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) tasks. Additionally, the paper presents results on bioinformatics datasets, which suggests that it may also fall under the category of computational biology (cs.SI).
